#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn55.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn55.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 55 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 55 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn55.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Rājakārāmavagga "
msgstr "2. A Thousand Nuns "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn55.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Brāhmaṇasutta "
msgstr "12. The Brahmins "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn55.12:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī "

msgctxt "sn55.12:1.2"
msgid "“Brāhmaṇā, bhikkhave, udayagāminiṃ nāma paṭipadaṃ paññapenti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, the brahmins advocate a practice called ‘get up and go’. "

msgctxt "sn55.12:1.3"
msgid "Te sāvakaṃ evaṃ samādapenti: "
msgstr "They encourage their disciples: "

msgctxt "sn55.12:1.4"
msgid "‘ehi tvaṃ, ambho purisa, kālasseva uṭṭhāya pācīnamukho yāhi. "
msgstr "‘Please, good people, rising early you should face east and walk. "

#. VAR: kaṇḍakaṭhānaṃ → kaṇḍakādhānaṃ (bj) | kaṇṭakaṭṭhānaṃ (s1-3) | kaṇṭakaṃ ṭhānaṃ (pts1) | kaṇḍakaṃ ṭhānaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: candaniyaṃ → candanikaṃ (bj, s1-3)
#. VAR: oḷigallaṃ → oligallaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn55.12:1.5"
msgid "So tvaṃ mā sobbhaṃ parivajjehi, mā papātaṃ, mā khāṇuṃ, mā kaṇḍakaṭhānaṃ, mā candaniyaṃ, mā oḷigallaṃ. "
msgstr "Do not avoid a pit, a cliff, a stump, thorny ground, a swamp, or a sewer. "

#. VAR: Yattha → yāni vā (si) | yattheva (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn55.12:1.6"
msgid "Yattha papateyyāsi tattheva maraṇaṃ āgameyyāsi. "
msgstr "You should await death in the place that you fall. "

msgctxt "sn55.12:1.7"
msgid "Evaṃ tvaṃ, ambho purisa, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissasī’ti. "
msgstr "And when your body breaks up, after death, you’ll be reborn in a good place, a heaven realm.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: bālagamanametaṃ → bālānaṃ gamanametaṃ (si)
msgctxt "sn55.12:2.1"
msgid "Taṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, brāhmaṇānaṃ bālagamanametaṃ mūḷhagamanametaṃ na nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "But this practice of the brahmins is a foolish procedure, a stupid procedure. It doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, or extinguishment. "

msgctxt "sn55.12:2.2"
msgid "Ahañca kho, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye udayagāminiṃ paṭipadaṃ paññāpemi; "
msgstr "But in the training of the noble one I advocate a ‘get up and go’ practice "

msgctxt "sn55.12:2.3"
msgid "yā ekantanibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati. "
msgstr "which does lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.362, sc3
msgctxt "sn55.12:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca sā, bhikkhave, udayagāminī paṭipadā; "
msgstr "And what is that ‘get up and go’ practice? "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.2"
msgid "yā ekantanibbidāya … pe … nibbānāya saṃvattati? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti—"
msgstr "It’s when a noble disciple has experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.4"
msgid "itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavāti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.5"
msgid "dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.6"
msgid "saṅghe … pe … "
msgstr "the Saṅgha … "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.7"
msgid "ariyakantehi sīlehi samannāgato hoti akhaṇḍehi … pe … samādhisaṃvattanikehi. "
msgstr "And they have the ethical conduct loved by the noble ones … leading to immersion. "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho sā, bhikkhave, udayagāminī paṭipadā ekantanibbidāya … pe … "
msgstr "This is that ‘get up and go’ practice "

msgctxt "sn55.12:3.9"
msgid "nibbānāya saṃvattatī”ti. "
msgstr "which does lead solely to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn55.12:3.10"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

